    • Constructor Detail

      • InfluxDBMetricObserver

        public InfluxDBMetricObserver(InfluxDBOperations influxDBOperations,
                              MetricTransformation... metricTransformations)
        This constructor creates an observer that forwards data in batches to an InfluxDB instance according to a configuration. It also allows for applying transformations to data point before it writing them to the database, such as appending additional tags. If no database exists with the name said in the configuration, it will be automatically created.
        Parameters:
        influxDBOperations - XXXX.
        metricTransformations - A list of closures allowing for transforming metrics before writing them to the database. The closure are applied in the same order they were passed as parameters.
